{
  "texts": [
    "In this section, we analyze the EUPcorrected cosmology from this perspective.",
    "First, we examine the phase space behavior using a dynamical systems approach.",
    "Then, we evaluate the effective sound speed to assess causal propagation and potential instabilities in perturbations.",
    "As discussed in Section 3, the EUP correction leads to an effective equation of state w(a) → -1 at late times, indicating that the EUP-induced fluid asymptotically behaves like a cosmological constant.",
    "This corresponds to the de Sitter limit with p = -ρ and a constant Hubble parameter H → H 0."
  ]
}